",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#ff7340]\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"📅\\\"}],\\\"2026-06-02\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#ff7340]\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"⏱️\\\"}],\\\"5 min read\\\"]}]]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bg-[#f5f5f5] py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-sm\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"max-w-7xl mx-auto flex items-center gap-2 text-gray-600 overflow-x-auto whitespace-nowrap\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L9\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-[#ff7340] transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Home\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"›\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L9\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/blog\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-[#ff7340] transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Blog\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"›\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-semibold text-gray-900 truncate\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"5 Signs You Need an Emergency Exterminator\\\"}]]}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"py-16 px-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"max-w-7xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"lg:col-span-8\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"article\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 prose-headings:text-[#0d1b2a] prose-a:text-[#ff7340]\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cp\\u003eSome pest problems can wait for a scheduled appointment, but others require immediate attention. Here are five signs you shouldn't ignore.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003e1. Daytime Activity\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eMost pests are nocturnal. If you see rodents, roaches, or bed bugs out in the open during the day, it usually indicates a severe infestation where hiding spaces are overcrowded.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003e2. Property Damage\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eChewed wires, gnawed furniture, or hollow-sounding wood are signs that pests are actively destroying your property.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003e3. Unusual Smells\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eA musty odor can indicate mice or roaches, while a sweet, rotting smell might be bed bugs.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003e4. Health Concerns\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eIf anyone in your household is experiencing unexplained bites, asthma flare-ups, or allergy symptoms, pests could be the culprit.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003e5. Rapid Reproduction\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003ePests like fleas and bed bugs multiply incredibly fast. A small problem today can become a nightmare tomorrow.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex justify-between items-center py-8 border-y border-gray-200 mt-16\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L9\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/blog\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-gray-500 hover:text-[#ff7340] transition-colors flex items-center gap-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-lg\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"←\\\"}],\\\" Back to Blog\\\"]}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-12\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h3\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-[#0d1b2a] mb-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Leave a Reply\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-gray-500 text-sm mb-6\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Your email address will not be published. Required fields are marked *\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"form\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"space-y-6\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"label\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\